translated: Friberg, Oswald Leonard, director, Jönköping, born December 14th, 1890 in Kalmar to field surgeon F.L. Friberg and Charlotta Fahlberg. Married to Barry Svenson in 18xx. Children: Birgit, born in 1928. Completed secondary school and technical elementary school, as well as specialized studies in technology and business subjects. Completed practical training in railway construction, workshops and electricity. Also completed drafting at the Navy Engineering Department and assembly and project management at an electrical engineering firm in addition to factory management at the match factories in Gothenburg, Lidköping, Mönsterås, Småland, Anneberg and Västervik. Served as a dispatcher in Gothenburg from 1929-1932 and also served as the managing director and owner of Gustaf Sandwall AB, Nogo AB, Linnarsson's Iron Works AB, and the Affärshuset in Jönköping AB. Held positions as a member of the board and secretary in the Jönköping Merchants' Association and as a member in the Swedish Industry Association, Swedish Chemical Industry Association, June Fair, chairman of the Eastern Storgatan Association in Jönköping, and a member in the Jönköping Building Materials Trade Association, Technical Association in Jönköping, Vätterbygd Electricians, Jönköping Conservative Council, Freemasonry, Par Bricole, Odd Fellows, Jönköping Hunting Association, and the Jönköping and Halmstad Golf Clubs, among others.
